					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">nineTENdo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">a hint to what opcode to study to do what needs to be done.</div><br /><br />It's no specific opcode -- each instruction/opcode only does a very small, generic task.  Actually doing something involves working with the right combination of several opcodes -- each doing a small part of a larger job.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">im just hoping there are easy answers to these questions</div>
<br />
<br />I think you'll find that once you have more of a grasp on programming fundamentals and understand 6502 a little more, you'll be able to answer these questions yourself.  It's not that the answers to these questions are difficult -- it's just that they require some existing understanding of NES operations.</div>

